  "texts": [
    "When represented by explicit matrices, the elements S 1,.",
    ", S s are usually called Stokes factors (or Stokes matrices) and the element h is the formal monodromy.",
    "There is a natural action of the group H on R Θ, which amounts to changing the framing.",
    "The representation variety actually has a richer structure: Theorem 3.9 ([Boa14, BY15]).",
    "The representation variety R Θ is a smooth affine complex algebraic variety, and is a twisted quasi-Hamiltonian H-space, with moment map given by µ: R Θ → H(∂), ρ → {ρ(∂)}, with ∂ referring to the loop around ∂ in the negative sense."
